---
import LegalLayout from '../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { withBase } from '../../lib/base-path';
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Accessibility"
  description="Accessibility statement for Richard Perez and EXIT Realty Central, including WCAG goals and support contact information."
  lastUpdated="June 10, 2026"
>
  <p>
      Richard Perez and EXIT Realty Central are committed to making this website usable by everyone,
      including people with disabilities. Access to housing information should not depend on how you
      browse the web.
  </p>

  <h2>Conformance goal</h2>
  <p>
      We aim to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1, Level AA. These
      guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible to people with visual, auditory, motor,
      and cognitive disabilities.
  </p>

  <h2>What we do</h2>
  <p>
      We build with semantic HTML, provide text alternatives for meaningful images, support keyboard
      navigation, maintain readable color contrast and visible focus indicators, and design pages to
      remain usable when text is resized or the page is zoomed. Automated accessibility testing runs as
      part of our build process, and we review pages manually as the site changes.
  </p>

  <h2>Known limitations</h2>
  <p>
      Some content provided by third parties — such as MLS/IDX listing data and embedded maps — may not
      yet fully meet these goals. We are working to improve those areas and can provide the underlying
      information in an accessible form on request.
  </p>

  <h2>Need something in another format?</h2>
  <p>
      If any part of this site is hard to use, or you'd like a listing, neighborhood guide, or document
      in a different format, contact Richard through our
      <a href={withBase('/contact')} style="color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 600;">Contact page</a>
      and we'll help promptly.
  </p>

  <h2>Reporting a barrier</h2>
  <p>
      We welcome your feedback. If you hit an accessibility barrier, use our
      <a href={withBase('/contact')} style="color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 600;">Contact page</a>
      and tell us the page and the problem. We aim to respond within one business day.
  </p>

  <p>
      This statement reflects our ongoing commitment to accessibility and to fair, equal access to
      housing. See also our <a href={withBase('/legal/fair-housing')} style="color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 600;">Fair Housing page</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
  